    • Printer

      public Printer(int printerId, StringBuilder sb)
      Initialize a print with a given ID and StringBuilder (where the all the info will be sent to)
      Parameters:
      printerId - The ID that will have our printer from now on
      sb - The StringBuilder that we'll use to keep the info of this printer transmitted
      Requires:
      sb != null
      Ensures:
      The info that this printer is online will be sent through the given StringBuilder

      private static int timeToFinishJobQueue(main.resources.Queue<main.java.Job> queue)

      Parameters:
      queue - The queue we want to inspect
      Returns:
      the time remaining to finish the printing of all jobs in a certain queue
      Requires:

      Ensures:
      \result >= 0

    • printCurrentJob

      public void printCurrentJob(int duration)
      Prints the current job for a given time, if there's any
      Parameters:
      duration - The time we want our Printer to be printing
      Requires:
      !isEmpty() && duration <= currentJob().getPrintingDuration()
      Ensures:
      this.currentTime will be updated accordingly to the given time (unless there's no current job)

      public boolean isEmpty()
      Returns whether our printer is empty of jobs or not
      Returns:
      true if there's no other job available in our printer, false otherwise

    • printForDuration

      public void printForDuration(int duration)
      Prints for a given time everything possible. If there's no Job available, it will simply increment the current time
      Parameters:
      duration - The given duration for the printer to be working
      Requires:
      duration >= 0
      Ensures:
      this.currentTime will be updated accordingly to the given time

    • printUntilTime

      public void printUntilTime(int time)
      Prints until a given time everything possible. If there's no Job available, it will simply increment the current time
      Parameters:
      time - The given time until when we want our printer to be working
      Requires:
      time >= currentTime()
      Ensures:
      this.currentTime will be updated accordingly to the given time
